cation Institutions -- tCorporate Education -- tEdTech - Future of Education -- tPart III: Creating a Future-Ready Learning Landscape -- tRiding the Waves of Change -- tAuthor Bios -- tVisual Thinker -- tSnapshots of the Contributors -- tVision Project Partners -- tPeople Who Shared With Us Their Vision -- tNotes0 aOpen Accessuhttps://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_abf2funrestricted online access2star  aEnvisioning the Future of Learning for Creativity, Innovation and Entrepreneurship outlines the work and findings of the Erasmus+ VISION research project. Education is changing and teachers and students around the world are reshaping it. This book is designed to help educators, policy makers and stakeholders from industry and society at large navigate the changing landscape of education for creativity, innovation, and entrepreneurship (CIE). Built on insights from more than 250 experts, the book presents a learning landscape that captures today's shifts within CIE education and proposes guidance and potential pathways for those involved in the field. The book shows that the landscape of education for CIE is influenced by: Learning as an immersive experience driven by play and experimentation The rise in on the job education and learning by doing as part of life-long upskilling Teachers' roles evolve to be coaches and mentors developing hard and soft skills Numerous images are included in the book using the technique of visual thinking, stimulating imagination, creativity and innovation.  aIssued also in print.  afunded by EU Erasmus+ Programme  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Entrepreneurship.2bisacsh  aFutu